<li>The Heritage Foundation--<a href="/heritage/news/pr121395.html">Hong Kong Has World's Freest Economy; Singapore 2nd; Taiwan Tied for 8th in 1996 "Index of Economic Freedom."</a>  December 13, 1995
<li>The Heritage Foundation--<a href="/heritage/news/pr12135a.html">Just 11 of 142 Countries Have Free Economies, Says 1996 "Index of Economic Freedom."</a>  December 13, 1995
<li>The Heritage Foundation--<a href="/heritage/news/pr12135b.html">Bahamas, Panama, Chile, El Salvador Have Latin America's/Carribean's Freest Economies.</a> December 13, 1995.
<li>The Heritage Foundation--<a href="/heritage/news/pr12135c.html">Just 5 African Nations Have Free Economies.</a> December 13, 1995.
<li>The Heritage Foundation--<a href="/heritage/news/pr121195.html">Clinton's Family Tax Cut Denies Tax Relief to 23 Million Children.</a>  December 11, 1995.
<li>Family Research Council--<a href="/townhall/FRC/press/120795.html">FRC calls on Congress to Support the Child Protection and Ethics Act of 1995</a>.  December 8, 1995.
<li>Family Research Council--<a href="/townhall/FRC/press/120795.html">It's Time We Knew What Happened to 
the Children of Table 34.</a> December 7, 1995.
