<center><h3>Comments</h3></center>
Brent (Baker):
<dd>Your April Fools' Issue (of Notable Quotables) was the best ever. For about the third time, you got me boiling and making notes for a column. I didn't catch on until I got down to Rather and Engberg.
<dd>Spouse and I have shown it to a score of newsfolk, all of whom bit on Bryant Gumbo. Satire only works when it's close to the truth.
<dd>Great Stuff.
<p>
-- E-mail from a nationally syndicated columnist and friend of the MRC.

